   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">This topic describes a use case for creating a flat rate billing program.</p>
         <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Standard Statement</uicontrol>
            </p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">This use case gives an example on how to create a flat rate billing program. You might use this functionality differently, depending on your business case.</p>
         </note>
         <p class="- topic/p ">This use case describes how an Agreement Analyst can create a flat rate billing program to achieve and align the specific billing requirements.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">In this case, an Agreement analyst or program manager creates flat rate billing programs for an account.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">To create a flat rate billing program, please follow the below steps:</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Create an agreement for an account.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Add one or more billing programs to the agreement.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Create a flat rate billing program of a specific sub-type.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Add products or categories or bundles to the program.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Specify one or more qualifications and benefits tiers for the product categories or bundles.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Add participants to the program.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol> the program.Agreement Manager approves the program. After the program is approved, Agreement analyst activates the agreement. Now, the program schedule is generated.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Billing analyst manages the Invoice Runs.</p>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
